'''Paolo Pedretti''' (22 January 1906 &ndash; 22 February 1983) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[Bicycle racing|cyclist]] who competed in the [[1932 Summer Olympics]]. He won the gold medal in the [[Cycling at the 1932 Summer Olympics <U+2013> Men's team pursuit|team pursuit event]].<ref name=sref>{{cite web|title=Olympics |url=http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pe/paolo-pedretti-1.html|publisher=sports-reference|accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref>

